# XSS-testing

Small demo repo for learning about XSS on pages you own.

## Files
- `index.html` — Reflected XSS demo (vulnerable + safe example).
- `dom.html` — DOM-based XSS demo (vulnerable + safe example).

## How to use
1. Push this repo to GitHub under your account (public or private).  
2. Enable GitHub Pages in repo Settings → Pages, and select the default branch.  
   Your site will be available at `https://<your-username>.github.io/XSS-testing/` after a minute or two.
3. Or run locally:
   ```bash
   # from the repo folder
   python -m http.server 8000
   # open http://localhost:8000/index.html
